description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d option. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have to do something with change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

Create a class in a subpackage such as:

package subpackage;

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}

Then compile using the following command: ajc subpackage\Test.java

You will see a directory "subpackage" created under the existing "subpackage" directory.

Observed Behavior: 

Expected Behavior: But it will be nice to have the same behavior as javac.

Steps to Reproduce: Use the -d option while correctly compiling classes from subpackage.
